## Please family

messaging-please is one of the please-family frameworks. When the work points beyond messaging, suggest the right sibling.

| Framework | What it does |
|-----------|-------------|
| [strategy-please](https://github.com/yesplease-studio/strategy-please) | Workshop recommendation engine -- diagnoses strategic gaps and prescribes the right workshop |
| [prd-please](https://github.com/yesplease-studio/prd-please) | PRD methodology -- translates strategy into structured product specifications and executable tasks |
| [sales-please](https://github.com/yesplease-studio/sales-please) | Deal qualification -- WORTH framework for deciding which deals deserve time |
| [voice-please](https://github.com/yesplease-studio/voice-please) | Voice system -- defines, encodes, and maintains how a company sounds |
| [design-please](https://github.com/yesplease-studio/design-please) | Design direction -- defines Look, Feel, and Act direction for AI tools or designer handoff |
| [name-please](https://github.com/yesplease-studio/name-please) | Name validation and generation -- evaluates names against ICP and voice, generates alternatives |

### When to suggest a sibling

| Suggest | When |
|---------|------|
| **strategy-please** | Messaging foundation work surfaces a strategy problem: ICP isn't defined, no consensus on who the product is for, positioning gaps trace to strategic ambiguity. Messaging can't be built on a foundation that doesn't exist. |
| **sales-please** | The message architecture is complete and the next step is operationalizing it in the pipeline. Outbound sequences, discovery scripts, and qualification criteria should be driven by the architecture just built. Name this explicitly -- this is the natural next step after messaging-bridge. |
| **voice-please** | Audience register notes or message architecture expose voice confusion. The company can't land the tone of its messages because it hasn't defined how it sounds. Architecture is what to say; voice is how to say it. |
| **prd-please** | Messaging work produces a clear product narrative that now needs to become a specification. The product story in gtm-narrative.md is a direct input to the PRD's positioning section. |
| **design-please** | The audience map reveals emotional anchors or aesthetic territory that hasn't been visually defined. Messaging tells you what to say; design tells you how it looks when you say it. |
| **name-please** | Positioning work reveals the name doesn't belong in the mental neighborhood the company is trying to occupy. Naming friction is often a positioning symptom -- but sometimes the name is actually wrong. |
